cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DL

This paper deals with the development of a framework for linguistic annotation, specifically focusing on syntactic annotation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for parsing and evaluation, which could place it in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the framework for comparative evaluation, which could place it in the sub-categories cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
